description: The US Africa Command carried out an airstrike in Puntland, Somalia, targeting IS-Somalia positions and killing several operatives. Coordinated with the Somali government, the strike occurred southeast of Bosasso port city. This attack is part of an ongoing counter-terrorism operation, with previous strikes eliminating key IS figures. No civilians were reported harmed.
title: US airstrikes in Somalia kill several Islamic State members

description: Hamas' armed wing released a video of Israeli hostage Elkana Bohbot, pleading with Prime Minister Netanyahu for his release after being held in Gaza for 540 days. Bohbot, captured during the October 2023 attack, questioned why the government hadn't secured the release of all hostages despite the ongoing conflict and bombing.
title: Hamas releases new video of Israeli hostage shouting and begging for release

description: Hamas agrees to a 50-day ceasefire proposed by Egypt, releasing five hostages including American-Israeli Edan Alexander. This follows the October 7, 2023 attacks. Israel has submitted a counter-proposal, seeking the release of 10 to 12 hostages. The conflict has resulted in significant Palestinian casualties.
title: Hamas agrees to release five hostages in renewed ceasefire, Israel counters

description: A small aircraft crashed into a residential home in Minnesota, resulting in the deaths of all passengers on board. The accident caused significant fire and smoke damage to the house. Minnesota Governor Tim Walz and the NTSB are coordinating to investigate the incident.
title: No survivors after small plane crashes into house in US' Minnesota, says official
Our linguistic diversity is a source of unity, not discord, says Rajnath Singh

description: Kiyan Anthony shined as the star player for Lutheran High School during The Throne basketball tournament, leading his team to an 83-56 victory over the William J. Brennan Bears in the semifinals. His parents, Carmelo and La La Anthony, were present to cheer him on.
title: Carmelo Anthony and La La Anthony are always ready to support their son Kiyan
AIADMK had negotiated alliance with Vijay's TVK months before warming up to BJP

description: Congress criticizes the Modi government for allowing banks to increase ATM withdrawal charges, along with a series of other levies on account holders. They argue that these measures have effectively turned banks into collection agents, extracting significant amounts from citizens through various banking fees and charges.
title: BJP has made banks collection agents: Congress on ATM charge hike

description: CBFC has ordered 17 changes to the Malayalam film 'Empuraan' starring Mohanlal due to backlash over its portrayal of the 2002 Gujarat riots. The changes were requested after criticism from BJP and RSS members, with the film's producers agreeing to make necessary edits to address concerns.
title: CBFC seeks 17 cuts as Mohanlal film stirs Kerala storm
Drunk man vandalises Veer Tejaji idol in Jaipur, arrested

description: Hamas has accepted a fresh Gaza ceasefire proposal mediated by Egypt and Qatar, urging Israeli support but refusing to negotiate on their armaments. Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu acknowledged the proposal and responded with a counter-proposal in coordination with the US. Negotiations continue as hostilities persist.
title: Hamas accepts fresh ceasefire proposal, Israel submits counter-offer

Why Rajasthan Day is changing calendars

description: The Gujarat high court cited Pink Floyd lyrics to highlight the customs department's decade-long inaction on show-cause notices issued to Rohan Dyes and Intermediates Ltd in 2009. The court quashed the notices due to the prolonged delay and criticized the authorities for failing to resolve the case since personal hearings in 2012.
title: Gujarat HC quotes Pink Floyd, quashes decade-old notices by customs
